\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. Yes, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, but not - not sort of each term, infrequently I would say, when the - often the headmaster would - ask - for a parents evening and then the
y would go to - those. They did have the - odd parents evening, graded not at the previous school, at the Musters Road school they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 This is the first parents meeting I've heard of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I think it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were they in advance of their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would think so, I - I - I think he was merely having a parents meeting because - he was interested in boys and he was interested in the parents of the boys, and not so much as the - modern parent - teacher meetings as they are today but rather to get to
 know the parents, and judge the boys attitude as a result of the background that he found by meeting the parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 This is just Musters Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Not at Trent Boulevard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did your parents met any of the other teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I think just the head, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Did the other children at these schools come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would say they came from - different types. The - all types, I - I think really except the - boys who'd gone to boarding school type - homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Did the teachers single out some children for different types of treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Only in - not in so far as educationally was concerned I think there were a certain amount of favouritism - with -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did this sort of show very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Only insofar as some boys could get away with what others couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Can you remember any instances or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, it's an impression that I - I've got that - of - of being a little discontented that I wasn't one of those who got away with things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Would there be any gangs or groups in these two schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Not the gangs as known as - as sort of modern type of gangs but - you had your little group of friends in the school, who - very often didn't agree with the other little groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well then there was generally a - arguments and very very occasionally - fisticuffs but - that was the exception rather than the rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were you caught with fisticuffs would anything happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh definite
ly, a caning - yes. Didn't matter whether it was outside school hours or not, you were still - hauled up for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were there any worse punishments than caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You didn't go to the headmaster and get the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Not 'til I got to the high school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Can you tell me what happened about going to the high school? Did you pass exams in those days to go or did you just apply to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I don't t
hink I could possibly have passed an exam to go. I'm pretty certain it was accepted - that the - that my wife's grandparents had been I know and - I had - various relations who'd been, and I think I was taken on sufferance as a result of this rather than 
- any particular ability.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Between eleven and twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You say you remember what the fees were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, three - fees then were three guineas a year. I'm sorry, a term. Term, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And it was just as it is now, private and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How did you get to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well I used to go from Bridgford on - on the - bus, and then walk from the market place - to the high school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How long did it take altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Nearly threequarters of an hour. Round about threequarters of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What were the hours then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Still had to be there for nine. Now let me think. There wasn't time to get home for a meal and back so that - I think we didn't - we finished roughly about half past twelve in the morning, and starte
d again at two in the afternoon, and finished at - four fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So what did you do about a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Stayed - stayed - at the school for meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you take it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, no. There - there was meals provided.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What were they like?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh like all school meals you know, nobody thought very much of them. And then in those days you - didn't have to pay so much a week, you - paid for your meal on the day you had it, so of course - quite a lot of the time the tuck shop had your lunch
 - money, and - you didn't have the - ordinary - lunch at the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 When you were at the high school were you there Saturday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 It's only just stopped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Has it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Well, I e
njoyed the school - there was - one master that - I didn't get on with at all, I don't think we liked each other at all. He once gave me a - a - in French a - piece of paper a little bigger than a postage stamp and told me to fill it on both sides, I fill
ed it on one and apologised I couldn't think of anything for the other and I got - in detention for a week for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 A week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh yes, I had to go every day for the week. And of course you had to take the car - the chit home for your father to sign
, that he knew you'd been in detention. Well I did the first three days and then it began to get a little hot at home, so I - I didn't take the other, and - I was told I would have to go and see the head as I hadn't got it signed, and then I think that - 
he thought perhaps detention for a week wouldn't be received well by the head, so he just scrubbed it and we heard no more about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did other people find him trouble some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I think possibly it was largely that - the German master used to write go
od reports of German, I seemed to be able to do that all right but French I didn't like the master and - I didn't do French well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What about the other teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh I got on - very well with the other teachers, we were caned at times - the German
 master was - also the rugger master. And - that's why you learnt German, because you were fond of rugger and you - had to please the German master, and - but he was always the least - breach of discipline was bend over and - the cane was duly - applied t
here, and - being a rugger master it was fairly vigorously as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What sort of things would you have been caned for there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh, talking behind his back when he was writing something on the blackboard - if you came in late - generally ordinary breaches of discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Quite small things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And detention was a form of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Detention was a form of punishment, but he always gave you the alternative, the detention or - the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 The German master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes, he always - gave you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 But the French master didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
But-the French master didn't, no, he - he - he - he had some what I felt were most unkind habits, you'd sit - with your hands on the hot pipes and he'd sit on your hands you know and - they 
weren't - they weren't sufficient to blister or anything but it - it really - you know, was very hot. He was - I had one curious thing with him because - I was so cross one day I said that when I'd left school I'd come back and give him a good hiding you 
see. And - the first - old boys dinner - I attended after leaving school, he came up and said, W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 rth, you haven't been back to give me that good hiding. And I said, no, I realized afterwards that I found out that you had been - university boxing champion an
d I decided I'd better not. By this time he was about sixty so it tickled him to death of course. But - after that we used to meet quite friendly when we met.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Can you think of any other odd punishments like that we might not have come across?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh
 - of course the other schoolboy - business of putting - books down behind before you got smacked, you - you didn't often get away with that one, but we did have one fellow who - it didn't matter how much he was punished, his - his face never altered the 
expression whatsoever, and the old rugger master who was the German master used to get so cross with this, because he expected you to - react with it and this boy didn't, and - he got very much more punishment than the rest of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they have things like lines in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes. You would - be given lines - in detention to do, whilst detention was on, sometimes - prefects of course would give you lines that you had to write at home and bring back the next morning. For any misdemeanour, they saw
 you larking about between - having left school, on the way home or - on the way to school in the morning, the prefects job was to see you behaved between - the city and the school. And if you didn't then you'd get a hundred or couple of hundred lines to 
do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 In these days did you have a school uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So if you had your cap off might you have been punished by the prefects?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I don't remember anybody being punished for not having their cap on, I should think it was very probably though - probable that they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You mentioned the strap when you reached the high school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, I don't remember a strap, it was always the - a cane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 From the headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Cane - I've never known the headmaster cane. He proba
bly did but - he didn't to me. But one always had to - the head would come in to detention - in the - when you were stayed in after school, and - see why and wherefore you'd been put in detention. Want to see the chit that you had to take home to sign.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did these teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh, I - manners particularly of course. General, I would say general behaviour was expected to be - extemporary really. Can't say it was but it was expected to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh yes, I had to - because they were very interested in the - the reports that at the end of each - term. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. What was the - what have you been doing - o
n any particular day they asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they visit that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I can't remember whether in the early days they had parents meetings. My - people certainly had been to the school because - school plays and that sort of thing they would support. I d
on't remember whether we had - parent meetings there. They - they'd meet - the - head and some of the masters at the cricket or the rugger matches and that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You were very keen on games, were you in all the teams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I always had the 
ability to be - sort of captains of second teams and only ever aspired to the first if they were shorthanded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Was it a very gamey school or more academic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well it was games, very definitely, as much as I would say - academically, and why I say t
hat because - when I wanted my son to go to the high school, he had, like me no very great brains you see, so I went to see the headmaster and said I'd like my son to come to school, you know, his grandparents had come and so on. And he said, well what's 
he like academically, you see, and I said I'm afraid he was rather like me, not too brilliant. Hm. What's he like at sports? Oh, I said, he's very good at sports. Well you've got to have a levelling in the school of this size so he - he got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes, I would say that - they were all - sort of middle class families.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Was everybody fee paying then, or were there any scholarships or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I think there were - v
ery few, but one or two scholarships in those days, from the local authority paid the - but they were very - very much less of course and later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, I don't think so. Except for my German friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were there any gangs or groups in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, I wouldn't - say there were any gangs at all but there was the usual - oh I suppose there'd be, what, a hundred boys going down to Bridgford or - fifty boys going down to Bridgford and - you'd go down in threes or fours of your own particular friends.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would have said there were odd ones who didn't fit in with the rest of the boys and - nobody took much notice of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I think it was only - somewhere between fifteen or sixteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Would you have stayed on longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, because I wanted to go into farming and want
ed to go from there to the agricultural college.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So what happened at fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well the - then I went from there to the agricultural college at Sutton Bonnington. And - I did - first of all two three month periods on - cheese making, dairying and that sense. And then I did twelve months - on the farming side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So where have we got to in terms of years now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would - roughly about seventeen I would think then, you know, sort of fifteen and a half going -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So we've passed 1918 have we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes. The last - few months I was there - no, it must have been a bit later than that because - the period that I was doing farming - there were several ex-officers - who had been - demobbed early straight after the 1918 - who were doing - sort of re
habilitation, they wanted to take up farming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
So can you tell me a little more detail about the agricultural college? Did you pay to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
This was rather an amusing actually. My father had - expected to pay. I had been there about three wee
ks when - I learnt from another fellow there that he had got in on a scholarship, he hadn't sat in the exams - that the local authority had - spare scholarships, so I promptly - wrote for a scholarship, didn't say I was there of course, and was duly grant
e
d a scholarship without any - exam whatsoever. And as a result of that I got a motor bike - because I'd saved the family whatever it would have to have spent at school, yes, so - that worked out very well because I was able to get home at weekends you see
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You lived in the college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I lived in the college but went home at weekends on the motor bike and came back on Sunday night sort of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I suppose you worked hours according to cows did you, were they very long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, I - I - the hour
s weren't very long because - they had a - a staff of people you see who - did the early morning milking and this sort of thing. And we were there largely - I should think seventy-five percent was written to twenty-five percent practical work there. Beari
n
g in mind that - I suppose seventy-five percent of the students were farmers sons who knew the general background. And I had one - vivid memory there was - on a paper on economics - they dealt with - the economics of a village. And - the night before the 
e
xam on this I'd swotted this particular thing up, and I could see every word of this you see and I sat down and I wrote this with the greatest of enthusiasm you see, that I must have done extremely well at. And there was another question on something else
 
which how many people - were on - a - now what is the term - threshing machine, and I'd - I'd never done anything on a thrashing machine, so I made a - sort of estimate and then added another one that I might have thought of if I'd known what he did. Well
 
- when the results came out I'd passed - on the agricultural practical side which I knew nothing about, and on the economic paper I'd failed. I couldn't believe this. So I went to the - fellow who dealt with the - and he went on to the university as well 
-
 at - you know, the main university, and he said well there's one very - easy answer to you Warth, you cribbed. But I said, I didn't crib. He said, look nobody could write a paper like that almost word for word who hadn't cribbed. I said, well I swotted t
h
e night before. He said, I don't believe you. And that was that. And I met him many times afterwards and - he said, well I'm sorry but nobody in my opinion could have possibly written a paper so - accurately to the book without cribbing. I was very fed up
 about that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How long did you remember it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Could you have done it a month later or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well I think I could but I was so annoyed at - the results of failing on something that I hadn't cribbed on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What was the discipline like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Not very strict. No, one was - expected and the majority of the - students were older, and particularly of course fellows from the Army were in their - sort of nineteen, twenty - years of age categories, twenty-ones, so that - the d
iscipline wasn't - strong at all. You were expected to behave, if you didn't turn up for a lecture - I don't think anybody would have said anything. They used to have outside lecturers in the form - a vet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 eri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 nary surgeon would come and deal with the vet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 inary side you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
What was your sort of social life like at this stage, you went home at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes. Otherwise - beyond - in the lighter evenings of course there was - funnily enough I played hockey there, which I always used to think was a c
issy game 'til I played it, you know, and - got knocked about on the ankles. I don't think there was - you just made your own - amusement with - two or three people you palled up with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 When you were at this stage did you spend Sunday any differently 
from how you told me before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well no, I was still expected to - except - not in the afternoon of course, Sunday school - school but I was expected to go to church in the morning and the evening because the family did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What did you do in your spare time in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Did I have any spare time really - no, I think - we played - hockey, we played tennis - at - whilst we were at the agricultural college.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And in the holidays what sort of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Holidays were - motor bik
e of course, dashing around on that and - very keen on tennis. I - I don't think there was any other - sport particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes, we made - friends that - you know, farmer friends that 
I - I knew for many years afterwards. We had one - of course we had a table at which there were twelve sitting for meals, and - the one - particular dislike - I had and he had similarly a dislike for me, he sat at one end and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. And he used
 to serve the meat and the vegetables his end, and I used to serve the - sweet my end. I never had any meat and he never had any sweet, all the time we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Which didn't you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I didn't get the meat ever. That was worse but he never got
 a sweet at all. And then of course we ended up - eventually by - deciding to have a scrap about this, so - in the common room, everybody, after lights out, all filtered down and made a ring you see, and - produced boxing gloves. And then we went at each 
o
ther you see. Had been doing this for two or three rounds when one of the masters came down you see. And his comment was, look, I don't mind you two knocking each other about, but for goodness sake stop this crowd yelling - all the rest of the college can
 
hear you see, so back he went and - that - there we were pummelling each other and dead silence from these - people watching. And next morning - I had a - a very swollen nose. He had a glorious black eye which couldn't be hidden, so of course - I suppose 
he'd already heard about this, Robinson the - head of the department fetched us up before him you see. Well - Warth, how did you hurt - get your nose in that state? Oh I'm sorry sir, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 tripped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070  up and fell down, hadn't time to stop myself from bumping my nos
e. Oh yes. He looked at the other man. How did you get that black eye? Oh, he said, I was very foolish, I let a door bang back and I didn't - realize it was coming until too late. Oh. Interesting. OH, I'm sorry for both of you, go and sit down. He knew ve
ry well what had happened. But he didn't want to make any fuss about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Was it patched up then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
A little better. We each respected each other a little more I think because neither of us really won the fight. And - but we were never friends of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Do you know why it started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would say it was purely instinct. Neither of us liked each other right from the first time we met, you know, somebody that didn't - you didn't like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you bring any of these friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, the odd one would - come home at a weekend just from the - Saturday morning 'til - or Friday night 'til the - Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you make any new friends who were girls at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, there were some girls at the - yes, agricultural colle
ge because I used to remember the Honourable Miss Versley who persisted in smoking a pipe, which was most - sensational in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 She was young was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Oh yes, only - only a youngster about - I suppose she was eighteen or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No, I don't think so, we were just - casual friends I would say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Only those who - the odd ones who were brought home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would say - yes - when I was home, just at weekends because then I would only be less than seventeen or - you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. Yes, I was expected to be home not later than ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 When did that go up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I would have said almost - expected to keep to somewhere near those hours - right up to the time I left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Which was when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 When I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 At this stage did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 No. I don't think so at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you have any views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I don't remember having any real feelings on the political side except - being Conservative, I suppose it was father was a Conservative you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And you were too young to vote in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How long were you at the agricultural college altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Eighteen months altogether. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 And then what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Then I went farming, and my father had bought a farm at Bradmoor. And I was there for two years. The trouble
 with the farm was it was only a - comparatively small farm, hundred acres, was that the land - was - a good half hour's to threequarters of an hour journey with horse and carts, to get from the land to the farm buildings. And - it was some years afterwar
d
s I - when I - gave it up and said this will never do, and went back to - business with my father, and it was years after he told me he only reason he bought the farm because the land was so far away he knew I wouldn't stick it and I'd have to come back t
o the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So it was you who wanted to go in for farming was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I wanted to go into farming. Yes. Yes, it was my - of course - his father was farming - one of his brothers was farming and - I suppose I just had the - wish to start farming.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So when you started what was your sort of job when you started farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes - well of course he had a farm bailiff in the - early stage - whilst I was there, and he was really in charge, in that I had to do ploughing and - milking and - I was -
 sort of learning the job to be - a proper farmer, rather than a theoretical one that I'd largely been at the college of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 We are post 1918 now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Could you just tell me the stages in your career fairly briefly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Mm. Two years farming. Then into the - business with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Well I suppose a - I would just be - a deputy to him, he was - sort of ran the business - and - then - eventually -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You were sort of management from the word go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I was management from the word go, yes. I - on the other hand I also kept my hand in in the sense to know what everybody did, I would go on a retail round when we had retail rounds, I would - when - lorrymen wouldn't go out because the fog was too thick a
nd the hospitals wanted milk I would take a lorry irrespective of - more or less to show them up and to make sure deliveries were made, that sort of thing, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 
primarily}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070  my job was management. Then - my father retired, and I became managing director for - a period of about - eight years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What sort of years are these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Mm, just trying to work this out. I would say - somewhere - from thirty-five to - forty - early forties. And - then - when war broke out, I was asked to - let me get this right - I wa
s then in the business until just before the last war, when - I was asked to take on - the chief warden's job, which was taking up most of the day, I used to go in the morning then from - eleven o'clock, I was only at business from half past eight 'til el
e
ven. Every day, and then the rest of the day I was - acting as a - voluntary chief warden for the city, and every other night used to spend all night at the control centre. Then when the war was over - we were having a good deal of industrial - feel - fee
ling and all this sort of thing going on, and at that time I was asked if I would - take on the - controller job which George McNess had - didn't want to take on again. So I accepted that appointment.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Controller of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Well it was Civil Defence th
en, from ARP it became Civil Defence. Then after - a few months there was a circular came up from the Home Office to the effect that - there wasn't a Controller any more, it was a whole time Civil Defence Officer. And I was asked to take this on and I - t
u
rned it down, said no, I wasn't interested. And then - we were having an awful lot of trouble with - the office and I was there from half past five in the morning 'til half past five at night, checking everything in and out to - ensure that what waste the
r
e should be and so on. And - within a fortnight this was back again and - all - sorts of troubles on and I - they rang me again, Wigman then asked me to go and see him, the then leader of the council, and I - was so fed up I said, yes, I'll - pack the who
le thing up and come on - to this job. So I was - whole time Civil Defence officer for eighteen years. And was - one of two advisors to the Association of Municipal Corporations on Civil Defence. I was on the panel of - that - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 panels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070  - main - most of th
e panels at the Home Office which - you know, ironed out the - procedures that were to be adopted by the various authorities, and altogether really I had quite an interesting period there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Were you a councillor as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Before that - I was on We
st Bridgford Council between the wars, for seven years. Oh I forgot to say I was made a Member of the Order of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}British Empire{\*\xmlclose}
. And - this was - this was in 194 - 3 I think. There was only two of us who were the first - two Civil Defence Officers in the cou
ntry who were up there. I don't know whether you'd like an amusing - tale about this because although in those days I had a uniform which was virtually a police uniform with a cap - you see. My opposite number from Sheffield, who - as there for this - MBE
 
award thing, at the Palace, he was in - the nearest thing I can say to a - well he was termed the Norwegian Admiral, it was such an extraordinary uniform, and when we - attended the Palace, and were in the queue waiting to go into the - sorted out into th
e
 rooms - flunky came along and fished him out of the - crowd that were waiting and took him to - almost the head of the queue. This intrigued me intensely, and I was a bit peeved that nobody had fetched me out you see, knowing full well there was somethin
g funny about this. And - this was true, that he was thought to be a Norwegian Admiral. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070  why he was pushed in the front, so as you can imagine he was always termed the Admiral after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Could you choose your own uniform roughly then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, at that time there was no - uniform for officers and - in our own case here the chief constable said, right, you are all special constable - constables, and therefore - I will have you in police uniforms. This caused a certain amount of troubles becau
s
e - you know, one of my officers would be going along and there's a a street accident and he - he - he'd ignore the thing and the people'd ring up and say a police officer's left the accident you see. But - then - whilst - I was chairman of the Civil Defe
n
ce Officers Society for a couple of years, during which time - they kindly - invited me to does at the Guild Hall, and - they were kind enough to sort of say well you know if you want to be a Freeman of the City of London, we will - arrange this, which th
ey did, which was quite an interesting - most interesting little ceremony. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 
Then - I finished with Civil Defence - when I was sixty-five, and - retire, then there was a circular came out which - in the meantime Civil Defence had been stood down very largely,
 then a circular came out which said that local authorities were to - not recruit volunteers but they were to - org - re-organise and - staff were to be trained and so on. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Well - the Town Clerk rang me up and he said that - they'd nobody in the establishme
nt at all who knew anything about Civil Defence, everybody had gone, would I go back and - get this organised for them. Well I said no. Thank you very much, and then when I told my wife - this happened to be in the autumn, she said, I'd like you out the w
a
y in the winter if it's only mornings - so I had to ring him back and say yes I'll come in the mornings. So I went back for mornings, in fact I arranged with him, I said, well look, I don't want tying down, if I want to come in the morning I'll come but i
f
 I don't come in the morning I'll come in the afternoon you see. And - I did this for twelve months and - my job then was to get - each of the departments organised for the wartime job you see, if war came what each department dropped and what each depart
ment had to take up and so on. Having - done that I said, right, that's it, and thank you very much, I - came back to retirement.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Did you quite enjoy going back then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, because fortunately - I knew the heads of various departments, one or two
 had changed but - they were very decent about it, and so I was able to - talk to them on a sort of equal footing, we got things going very well. I know of some of the CDO's had difficulty with departmental heads who wouldn't - work at all with them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Looking back would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, because I think I've always been interested in people, and - with the result I met a tremendous number of people, and because during the war on - the Civil Defence side, on the ARP
 side in those days - I had something like a hundred and twenty-seven officers and - you know, several thousand people one knew, and - enjoyed the contact with people, and I have since because I'm still interested as chairman of the Royal Institution for 
the Blind, and - voice-chairman of the prison, I still - meet people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You are vice-president of what at the prison?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Vice - it's vice-chairman of the prison visiting committee, who are responsible for - punishment of prisoners misdemeanours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Have you been that a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Oh yes, I've been - it must be - more than ten years now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 What sort of drew you to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I think - I think I was invited by another fellow on the committee who said that - there's no kudos in those but
 you'll feel some satisfaction of trying to - be of some help, and - so I went along and - and - I - I have found it interesting. You are at times able to help prisoners. More often you're punishing them than helping them I'm afraid because you had to dea
l with all escapees and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Looking back do you ever regret the farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
I have sometimes wished that I had - stayed in farming, but - I don't think so really, I think that - my bent was - enjoying - knowing people and lots of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
In this period just before 1918 did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, I would say that prior to that that - workers and employers worked very much closer together than they ever have done - since of course since the - unions have made more battle grounds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
At that stage did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers? Did you know enough about it as you were a student and not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Well I saw a lot of it of course when m
anaging from the - dairy trade point of view, and - no, I - I would say in the main that - the - king pin of course was your foreman. If your foreman were - the type that - could get on with your staff and at the same time work with you - then the whole -
 
show was a happy shop. If you had a foreman who - either disliked management or - or - disliked - certain employees then you were in trouble, and you had to replace him and get somebody who was reliable - and be intermediary between the - top and the bott
om sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Before the end of 1918 you knew a bit about your father's work did you, did you go in the holidays to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes. We had a number of branches in those days at Scarborugh, Bridlington, Harrogate, Hull and - so on, and - of course 
there was no - modern refrigeration type in those days, so that - all surplus milk was sent to Nottingham to be made up into cheese. And you can imagine some very hot days what it was like. It was sour and it was - you know - terrible. And of course it us
ed to make some terrible cheese. Very acid cheese which was sold to - market traders who - went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mansfield{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and these sort of places and this was taken up by the miners who bought it rather cheaply of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Do you know then how foremen were appointed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You say so much hinges on the foreman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, Largely they were appointed - as a result of considered ability in the job of the roundsman or - or deliveryman. The interesting thing, it didn't apply in Nottingham but - my father was a director of - Marshal's Dairies in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and they couldn't get a promotion to foreman out of any of the men. They made so much - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7286430\charrsid6298070 illegitimately}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
 on their rounds by overcharging housewives on retail side, that not one of them would take a foreman's appointment. Mm. And they always had to go outside for their foremen. But it was simply because the housewives never checked how much milk they'd had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Some people say in those days there was a great deal of division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
Yes, we had - well it was - we've done the tinsmith department, the - the - they - made coolers, repaired churns and all this sort of thing, and they were of course craftsmen and - they have considered themselves above 
the dairy - staff who worked below, they had a - workshop above.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 You said you were born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, how many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Well we moved, I would say, within twelve months to Grays in Essex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 For another four years. And then we moved to - West Bridgford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 So you were roughly five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Do you know why you moved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes, because my father was originally - on the railway. And moved from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to Grays, and then he left the railway and joined his brother in - the home - in the dairy business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 I had a brother who died before I was born. And I had - one sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Do you know roughly what the age gap was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Yes, my sister was six years older than I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6116303 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 
No, I don't, I don't know whether I can work it out. I would think in the - round about the age of thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4413364 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9184678\charrsid6298070 Where did he come from?
